<TITLE> Two 'heroin smugglers' remanded </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 13 (bdnews24.com)  Police Tuesday took two "heroin smugglers" into five-day remand, a day after they were arrested at Zia International Airport Monday. Sub-inspector Md Zillur Rahman of the Airport Police Station appealed to the Chief Metropolitan Magistrate's Court for Dhaka for seven-day remand for the two: Ariful Islam Bhuiyan and Mahmud Ali Kafil. Additional chief metropolitan magistrate Shawkat Ali approved five days. In the remand appeal, police said the two were members of an international heroin smuggling cartel. Customs officials and members of a taskforce Monday arrested them and seized 16 packets of heroin, each weighing one and a half kilograms, from them. They were bound for China. The Department of Narcotics Control estimates that the heroin would have retailed for Tk 23.5 crore. bdnew
